# Rule 01: Structure

## Junior's Working Memory

Junior maintains persistent memory in `.junior/`:

```
.junior/
├── specs/          # Feature specifications (numbered: spec-1-name, spec-2-name, etc.)
├── experiments/    # Experiments (numbered: exp-1-name, exp-2-name, etc.)
├── research/       # Technical research documents
├── decisions/      # Architecture Decision Records (ADRs)
└── docs/          # Reference documentation
```

### Spec Structure
```
.junior/specs/spec-{N}-{name}/
├── spec.md                    # Main specification
├── spec-lite.md               # Condensed for AI context
├── user-stories/              # Implementation tasks
│   ├── README.md              # Progress tracking
│   └── spec-{N}-story-{M}-{name}.md
├── sub-specs/                 # Technical details (if needed)
└── docs/                      # Spec-specific documentation (if needed)
```

### Experiment Structure
```
.junior/experiments/exp-{N}-{name}/
├── experiment.md              # Main experiment doc
├── user-stories/              # Implementation tasks
├── findings/                  # Learning capture
└── research-links.md         # Related work
```

### Numbering Convention
- Specs: `spec-1-name`, `spec-2-name` (simple sequential)
- Experiments: `exp-1-name`, `exp-2-name` (simple sequential)
- Stories: `spec-1-story-1-name`, `spec-1-story-2-name` (simple sequential)

## Project Organization

```
.cursor/
├── rules/       # Numbered rules (00-junior.mdc, 01-structure.md, etc.)
└── commands/    # Slash commands for Cursor

junior/          # Source documentation
├── persona.md
├── philosophy.md
└── style-guide.md
```

## Working Principles

1. **Plan before implementation** - Create specs, get approval, then execute
2. **Work incrementally** - Vertical slices, build iteratively
3. **Document decisions** - Capture reasoning in `.junior/` for persistence
4. **DRY** - Never duplicate, reference existing content

## Rule Numbering

Rules must be numbered: `00-junior.mdc`, `01-structure.md`, `02-communication.md`, etc.

Core rule `00-junior.mdc` is always applied first.

